<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb581d959-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s286b–1"><num value="286b–1">§ 286b–1.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subpart—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb581d95a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s286b–1/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the term “medical library” means a library related to the sciences related to health; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb581d95b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s286b–1/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the term “sciences related to health” includes medicine, osteopathy, dentistry, and public health, and fundamental and applied sciences when related thereto.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb581d95c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title IV, § 470, as added <ref href="/us/pl/99/158/s2">Pub. L. 99–158, § 2</ref>, <date date="1985-11-20">Nov. 20, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/860">99 Stat. 860</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
